comments.message:
I guess this is different Patch 41113 where BMC is the responder for GetPDR. It makes sense to defer in the case of responder, where action for a request is long running and send the response and take the action.

In this class though BMC is reading the HostPDRs by issuing GetPDR. So I am not convinced whether we need to Defer sending the next GetPDR request. Even if you Defer, event loop will schedule it again. So the flow I am thinking is something like this. Let me know if I have misunderstood any performance considerations.

registerRequest(GetPDR, respHandler)

respHandler
{
Process GetPDR response;
Send the nextPDR request
}

> also does adding a deferred event cause any performance issue?
I don't think there is a performance hit, if you defer. It is more like I have 2 tasks, Task 1 is urgent which I will run now and Task 2 can happen later instead of Task1 + Task2
